news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body mulls special squad to curb construction plan violations
news.para: The officials are finding deviations from the approved online plan during the construction phase in several instances. This could be due to some people uploading doctored documents to meet the requirements and get online approvals.

news.title: Property survey in Secunderabad Cantonment moves at snail's pace
news.para: This census survey is aimed at enumerating every property in the Cantonment based on the inputs received from the drone survey, taken up under the Survey of Villages and Mapping with Improvised Technology in Village Areas (Svamitva) scheme.

news.title: Hyderabad: No takers for recycled materials, builders cite logistics and hold-up
news.para: The two C&D plants set up by GHMC at Jeedimetla and Fathullaguda process 1,000 tonnes of debris daily, and produce bricks, sand, and rock aggregates, which even the civic body itself doesn't utilise.

news.title: Keystone in talks to redevelop projects in Mumbai
news.para: In addition to these redevelopment projects, the company is also in advanced discussions to enter into an agreement to jointly develop three projects in prime areas of the country’s commercial capital.

news.title: DHFL promoters set up 87 shell companies, says CBI charge sheet
news.para: Taking cognisance of the charge sheet, a special CBI court last week ordered that all 75 accused in the case be summoned. "Investigation at the overseas level has also to be conducted to trace the trail of funds of DHFL," said the court order.

news.title: Table Space raises $300 million in funding from Hill House to expand its operations
news.para: "Table Space has signed some large clients recently and has been looking for funding to expand its business. The fresh funding will help them expand at a faster pace," said multiple people aware of this transaction.

news.title: MREAT directs Runwal Homes to pay a homebuyer interest on amount paid
news.para: The couple had booked a flat for a consideration of about Rs 1.61 crore, on the 37th floor of a building in the Runwal Greens project in Nahur.

news.title: Gurugram: Residents protest against Central Park over restricted access to facilities
news.para: The residents alleged that they have been denied access to facilities, including central greens, club, even after more than a decade of taking the possession.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body raps architects' body for silence on draft development plan
news.para: ​​The civic body has asked why the IIA remained silent for about 30 years on the draft DP which could have been finalised long back. The IIA responded saying they are raising issues which are in the interest of Navi Mumbai.

news.title: AAI may lose three floors to pave way for fourth runway at IGI Airport
news.para: The permission from AAI to demolish three floors is awaited, but nearly 750 employees of this building have already been shifted to a new location.

news.title: Jaipur: Metro Enclave plot owners to receive lease deeds soon
news.para: “Since the agreement has been signed, our priority will be to hand over the lease deeds to the 120 plot owners as early as possible as our next course of action,” said a JDA official. JDA will have to pay Rs 318 crore to JMRC for the transfer of land.

news.title: Karnataka HC refuses to quash case against residents for obstructing officials
news.para: Dismissing the petition filed by Uma Shankar Mohapatra and 22 others, Justice K Natarajan noted there is prima facie material to show (as depicted in photographs/video clippings) that there is a cognisable offence for conducting investigation against the petitioners.

news.title: Chandigarh administration sees little room for change in additional FAR rates
news.para: Meanwhile, deputy commissioner-cum-estate officer Vinay Pratap Singh said, “The issue is still under consideration and no final decision has been taken.”

news.title: SWAMIH fund approves Rs 207 crore for Sikka group project in Greater Noida
news.para: The last-mile funding, first instalment for which released recently, will lead to time-bound delivery of houses to 1,000 home buyers at Sikka Kimaya greens.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Another FIR against promoters of Popular Builders
news.para: Ramkrushna Acharya said that Raman and Dashrath along with an unknown man, Saryudasji Bava, forged papers for the land deal in the name of Ramkrushna's grandfather, and occupied the plot measuring around 63,772 square metres.
